 given the level of inputs.", "\"PRODUCTIVITY\":\"Productivity is the measure of the efficiency of production, often expressed as the ratio of output to input.\"", "\"RESOURCE UTILIZATION\":\"Resource Utilization\" is a dimension of Fitzgerald and Moon's Building Block Model that measures how effectively a company's resources, particularly staff, are used. It encompasses the extent to which resources such as labor and machinery are utilized effectively. Additionally, resource utilization evaluates various aspects of business activity, including non-productive time, hours of operation with no customers, and the number of meals served per seat.", "\"CAPACITY\":\"Capacity is the maximum output that a production system can achieve under normal conditions.\"", "\"LEAD TIME\":\"Lead Time is the total time it takes from the initiation of a process to its completion, including production and delivery.\"", "\"CYCLE TIME\":\"Cycle Time is the time it takes to complete one cycle of a production process from start to finish.\"", "\"BOTTLENECK ANALYSIS\":\"Bottleneck Analysis is the process of identifying and analyzing the bottleneck in a production system to improve overall performance.\"", "\"CONSTRAINT ANALYSIS\":\"Constraint Analysis is the process of identifying and managing constraints in a system to optimize performance.\"", "\"PRODUCTION SCHEDULING\":\"Production Scheduling is the process of planning and organizing the production process to ensure efficient use of resources and timely delivery of products.\"", "\"RESOURCE ALLOCATION\":\"Resource Allocation\" is the process of assigning available resources to various tasks and activities to optimize production and achieve business goals. It involves distributing financial, human, and material resources to various projects or departments. Effective allocation is crucial for achieving sustainability goals and optimizing performance. The process aims to distribute available resources among various uses in an optimal way.", "\"PROCESS OPTIMIZATION\":\"Process Optimization is the practice of improving production processes to increase efficiency, reduce costs, and enhance product quality.\"", "\"LEAN MANUFACTURING\":\"Lean Manufacturing is a production philosophy that focuses on minimizing waste and maximizing value by continuously improving processes.\"", "\"SIX SIGMA\":\"Six Sigma is a data-driven methodology for improving quality by identifying and eliminating defects in production processes.\"", "\"KAIZEN\":\"Kaizen is a Japanese term meaning 'continuous improvement,' and it involves making small, incremental changes to improve processes over time.\"", "\"JUST-IN-TIME (JIT)\":\"Just-in-Time (JIT) is a production strategy that aims to reduce inventory and increase efficiency by producing goods only as they are needed.\""], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}